<promed@promedmail.org>
[Byline: Jamie Walker]
[The situation in Emerald is deteriorating into legal actions and
countersuits. Clearly, illegal importation of planting material into
Australia from abroad is a gross violation of the International Plant
Protection Convention. This is a classic example of circumventing the
rules. Unfortunately, the citrus growers in Queensland are strapped to find
ways to dispose of their crop through the usual routes. - Mod.DH]
